The paper focuses on implementing a spiking CNN for image classification, which falls under the intersection of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the learning capabilities and catastrophic forgetting in the spiking CNN, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions power usage reduction, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY).
